# Seeds — {{RUN_NAME}}

Hand-authored investigation questions. The pipeline will REJECT a run that does not replace the template placeholders below with real domain-specific seeds.

Each seed must be:
1. **Testable** — it can be answered by querying the corpus with concrete operators.
2. **Scoped** — it names specific units/collections/fields the adapter will touch.
3. **Grounded** — it states what evidence would support, refute, or leave it ambiguous.

Minimum: 3 P1 seeds, 2 P2 seeds, 1 P3 seed. Realistic: 20+ P1, 6+ P2, 4+ P3. More domain knowledge upfront = sharper findings.

---

## §0 Evidence base seed (REQUIRED FIRST if your corpus has user-level analytics)

**T000: Denominator accounting.** Compute the total count of units (users / documents / sessions / files) and the subsets that downstream findings will reference. Example subsets: "users with >=1 substantive record", "documents with non-empty field X", "sessions lasting >N seconds". Every P1/P2/P3 percentage must reference one of these denominators explicitly — no bare "X% of users" claims.

